race.comment: FUADEE (1) faced the starter for only the second time and was coming off a five-week let-up when a tiring fourth over this distance at Wyong last start. Will tighten right up following that outing and this looks an ideal race for him. BARKING MAD (14) last appeared 45 days ago when he worked home fairly to be beaten under three lengths in a 1400m Warwick Farm maiden. Bred to be very good and this might be a nice launch pad for better things ahead. SEMIBREVE (8) was ridden a bit closer to the pace last time and boxed on well for second over 1300m at this track. Has a wide gate to contend with but if things go her way she is a great chance to break through. KISSAVOS (4) did some work early after a poor jump and had nothing left last start over 1000m here. Probably needs this trip now so he is worth another chance. TENNESSEE DOLLY (13) did his best work late on debut at Gosford recently. Suited by an extra 100m today so must go in the numbers.
